hint:"The first Islamic caliphate that spread Islam across the Middle East and Persia",
hint_pt:"O primeiro califado islâmico que espalhou o Islã pelo Oriente Médio e Pérsia",
facts:[
  "The Rashidun Caliphate (632–661 CE) was the first Islamic state after Muhammad's death, led by four 'Rightly Guided Caliphs': Abu Bakr, Umar, Uthman, and Ali. Within 30 years it conquered the entire Sassanid Persian Empire, took Egypt and the Levant from Byzantium, and became the largest empire in the world at that time.",
  "The Rashidun period established foundational Islamic governance, law and military organization. It ended with the First Fitna (Islamic Civil War) when Ali was assassinated in 661 CE, leading to the split between Sunni and Shia Islam that persists to this day. Muawiyah I then founded the Umayyad Caliphate."
],
facts_pt:[
  "O Califado Rashidun (632–661 EC) foi o primeiro estado islâmico após a morte de Maomé, liderado por quatro califas. Em 30 anos conquistou o Império Sassânida Persa e tomou o Egito e o Levante de Bizâncio.",
  "O período Rashidun estabeleceu a governança islâmica fundamental. Terminou com a Primeira Fitna quando Ali foi assassinado em 661 EC, levando à divisão entre o Islã Sunita e Xiita."
],
