  "The Umayyad Caliphate (661–750 CE) was the largest empire in history up to that point, stretching from the Iberian Peninsula (Al-Andalus / Spain and Portugal) across North Africa, the Middle East and Persia all the way to the Indus Valley in modern Pakistan. Arabic was standardized as the administrative language across this vast region.",
